annotation 1 [[0.54, 0.22]] MaaS stack (Transport Integration, Situational Services, Mobility Hubs) is where consumer behaviour is driving real evolution — left-to-right pressure from post-COVID demand.
annotation 2 [[0.38, 0.40]] Regulation carries inertia: lags consumer-driven modes above it (Shared, Distributed Public) and the MaaS layer.
annotation 3 [[0.76, 0.72]] Zoom and virtual alternatives are Product/Commodity — they permanently displace a slice of commute demand.
annotation 4 [[0.18, 0.60]] Transport Infrastructure carries inertia: 30-50y asset lifecycles mean road/rail networks cannot evolve at consumer-behaviour speed.
annotation 5 [[0.68, 0.82]] Private Mode (car) is Commodity but under cost pressure from fuel prices (Ukraine shock, May 2022) and climate policy.

note SHOCKS: COVID, fuel, climate [0.92, 0.10]
